Activity Name: Tapering for a marathon is like switching your game difficulty settings to easy mode
Rolling some short doubles this week

Description: Ouch, this one was tough. Ran 2:28 the hard way, 1:13:17/1:14:57. Pacing through 20k was right on for 2:26 and I had a good pack to work with but even so, the effort always felt a little harder than I wanted it to. After 20k the group dropped me on the hill and it was a tough next 10k. Thankfully the bad patch ended at 30k and I was able to find another gear physically and mentally. I rallied to get back to low-3:30/k pace, telling myself that I still had a shot at a personal best if my shoddy mid-race math was right and if I pushed hard. I hung on for a PB and despite missing the Olympic standard, I'm proud of my effort out there. I wanted more, but the way it played out on the day I think it also could have gone a whole lot worse. Sometimes you just have to tough it out and finish the damn thing.  OK, recap done, I need a beer!
